public UpdateScmFromGitOrigin(@Nullable Boolean addIfMissing) {
    this.addIfMissing = addIfMissing;
    this.updateOnlyRoot = null;
}
```

But then the recipe YAML/declarative form can't set `updateOnlyRoot` unless we also have a two-arg constructor or use `@Builder`.

Hmm, let me think... The cleanest approach for this codebase is to use a static factory method or to not use `@Value` and just manually create the class. But that's a big change.

Actually, the simplest proper fix is: just add a single-arg constructor that delegates. But Lombok `@Value` already generates the all-args constructor. If I add ANY constructor, Lombok won't generate one. So I need to manually write BOTH constructors (one for backward compat, one for the full API).

