If I add a custom constructor, Lombok won't generate the all-args one. But the YAML/declarative recipe configuration uses the no-arg constructor + setters OR named constructor parameters. Let me check how OpenRewrite handles this...

Actually, looking at the `@Option` annotation, these are typically set via the constructor in OpenRewrite because `@Value` makes them constructor parameters. When OpenRewrite creates recipes from YAML, it likely uses the all-args constructor with named parameters.

Let me just manually write a constructor that takes both params and also manually add a convenience single-arg constructor:

Actually wait, I just realized there might be a simpler approach. What if I just add a single-arg constructor that Lombok's `@AllArgsConstructor` supplements? No, Lombok won't generate `@AllArgsConstructor` if any constructor exists.

